{"questionId":"33389619","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>A second line <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>M</mi></math> is parallel to <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>Π</mi></math>.</p>\n<p>The line <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>M</mi></math> passes through the point <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>)</mo></math> and intersects the <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>z</mi></math>-axis.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find the equation of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>M</mi></math>, expressing your answer in the form <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">s</mi><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">c</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>μ</mi><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">d</mi></math>, where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>μ</mi><mo>∈</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ℝ</mi></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>METHOD 1</strong></p>\n<p>recognition that the direction <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>M</mi></math> is from the point&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>4</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>1</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>2</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></math> and a point on the <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>z</mi></math>-axis <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>0</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>0</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mi>z</mi></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></math><em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>direction of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>M</mi></math> is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mo>±</mo></mfenced><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>4</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>1</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>2</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>z</mi></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></math><em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>(A1)</strong></em><br>the direction of the normal of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>Π</mi></math> is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>6</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>5</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></math> (seen anywhere)<em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>attempt to use the scalar product with their normal and their direction vector and equate to <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn></math><em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>4</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>1</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>2</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>z</mi></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced><mo>·</mo><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>6</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>5</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>⇒</mo><mn>24</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>10</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>5</mn><mi>z</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>z</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>31</mn><mn>5</mn></mfrac></math><em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mi>p</mi></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mi>q</mi></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mi>r</mi></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>4</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>1</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>21</mn><mn>5</mn></mfrac></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></math></p>\n<p>attempt to express equation in the form <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">s</mi><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>4</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>1</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>2</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mi>μ</mi><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mi>p</mi></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mi>q</mi></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mi>r</mi></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></math><em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">s</mi><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>4</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>1</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>2</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mi>μ</mi><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>4</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>1</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>21</mn><mn>5</mn></mfrac></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">s</mi><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>4</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>1</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>2</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mi>μ</mi><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>20</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>5</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mo>-</mo><mn>21</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></math><em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>METHOD 2</strong></p>\n<p>let the equation of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>M</mi></math> be <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>M</mi><mo>:</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">s</mi><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>4</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>1</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>2</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mi>μ</mi><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mi>p</mi></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mi>q</mi></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mi>r</mi></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></math></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note</strong>: Consideration of the <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>z</mi></math>-axis intersection and consideration of direction may be done in either order and marks should be awarded independently.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>recognition <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>M</mi></math> intersects the <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>z</mi></math>-axis where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math><em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>μ</mi><mi>p</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>μ</mi><mi>q</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn></mrow><mi>p</mi></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mi>q</mi></mfrac><mo>⇒</mo><mi>p</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>q</mi></math><em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>(A1)</strong></em><br><br>the direction of the normal of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>Π</mi></math> is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>6</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>5</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></math> (seen anywhere)<em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>attempt to use the scalar product with their normal and their direction vector and equate to <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn></math><em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mi>p</mi></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mi>q</mi></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mi>r</mi></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced><mo>·</mo><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>6</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>5</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>⇒</mo><mn>6</mn><mi>p</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><mi>q</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>5</mn><mi>r</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math><br><br></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>6</mn><mo>(</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>q</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><mi>q</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>5</mn><mi>r</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>⇒</mo><mn>21</mn><mi>q</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>5</mn><mi>r</mi></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mi>p</mi></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mi>q</mi></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mi>r</mi></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>20</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>5</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mo>-</mo><mn>21</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;(or any multiple of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>20</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>5</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mo>-</mo><mn>21</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></math>)<em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>(A1)<br></strong></em><br>attempt to express equation in the form <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">s</mi><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>4</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>1</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>2</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mi>μ</mi><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mi>p</mi></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mi>q</mi></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mi>r</mi></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></math><em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>(M1)</strong></em><br><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">s</mi><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>4</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>1</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>2</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mi>μ</mi><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>4</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>1</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>21</mn><mn>5</mn></mfrac></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">s</mi><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>4</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>1</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>2</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mi>μ</mi><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>20</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>5</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mo>-</mo><mn>21</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></math><em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[7 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"33389619","referenceCode":"24N.2.AHL.TZ0.11d","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Find the equation of M, expressing your answer in the form s=c+μd, where μ∈ℝ.","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"d","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 7]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","AHL 3.14—Vector equation of line","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","AHL 3.17—Vector equations of a plane","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","AHL 3.18—Intersections of lines & planes"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}